{"/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_fluorite_ver01/data/sn84020097/00332897652/1930053001/0580.xml":{"full_text":"Page Two\nFASCIST FISH TO LEAD\n\u201cRED PROBE\u201d TO HIDE\nHUNGER, WAR MOVES\nCommittee Composed of Southern Lawyers\nNoted for Their Black Reactionism\n\u201cRed\u201d Scare Hearings to Begin This Summer\nand Include the \u201cDaily Worker\u201d\nWASHINGTON, D. C., May 29\u2014'\nNicolas Longworth, speaker of the\nHouse of Representatives, whose\nfamily fortune was made from rent\nals of the old \"red light district\u201d;\nof Cincinnati, yesterday appointed;\nthe \u201cinvestigation\u201d committee which 1\nis to try to cover up growing unem\nployment under a cloud of \u201cred\nplots\u201d and to continue the use of the\nWhalen forgeries as material to whip\nup propaganda for war against the,\nSoviet Union.\nThat this is the purpose of the j\nHoover regime for which Longworth\nacts, is seen in the naming of J.;\nHamilton Fish, New York fascist,\nwho spoke in the fascist May Dayj\nanti-Communist meeting at Union\nSquare, as chairman of the Anti-\nCommunist Committee. In such\ncommittees, the chairman usually is\nthe boss of the committee, the others\nbeing mere stuffing.\nHowever, the remarks of Fish in\nthe House, when the resolution to\nappoint the committee was adopted,\nshowed that the fascist Fish looked\nfor the Southern capitalists\u2019 sup\nport, hence three of the committee\nmembers are from the South, show- j\ning that the Hoover administration\nis working with Fish on the affair.\nAll of the Committee are lawyers\nand of course none has ever even\nbeen a worker.\nBeside? Fish, those appointed\nwerei John Edward Nelson of Maine,\na republican, Rotarian and 32 tie- 1\nFord \u201cSolves\u201d Crisis by More Overproduction\nHenry Ford, whose niche in the hall of fame is assured by his\nbrilliant discovery that history is bunk, has made another bid for uni\nversal. admiration.' This time it is in the field of economics. Accord\ning t*> this versatile ignoramus, the quickest way to get out of the\npresent crisis of overproduction is to proceed to overproduce still more,\nboth in agriculture and manufacturing.\nNotorious as a slimy hypocrite. Ford advises his fellow exploiters\nagainst wage cuts at the present time, \u201cwhen the country is down..'\nand admits that \u201cwages are too low everywhere.\u201d And still they say\nthat the brains are all on the side of the bosses!\nVote Muscle Shoals t\nFollowing the Hoover Wall\nStreet administration policy of\nturning the country\u2019s resources\nover to the big trusts and corpora\ntions, the House of Representa\ntives adopted a plan Wednesday\nSenate in Secret Study of Secret Data\nThe Senate Foreign Relations Committee closed its hearings on j\nthe London Naval Treaty yesterday. It will now spend about a week\nstudying in secret the secret correspondence that passed between the\nState and Navy Departments and the American delegation to the\nLondon Conference. Wall Street\u2019s Government does not want the J\ncontents of this correspondence revealed to the American masses, as\nit would immediately expose the actual war preparations and the real\nboss class interests behind the \u201ctreaty Hoover is rushing the ratifi-\ncation of the treaty by calling a special session of the Senate some\u25a0\ntime in June.\nV\nVote on Sham Anti-Injunction Bill\nThe Shipstead bill to \"outlaw\u201d\nyellow dog contracts and to prevent\nFederal Courts from issuing injunc\ntions aganst all but real, militant\nstrikes conducted under the revolu\ntionary leadership of the Trade j\nUnion Unity League was sent to the 1\nJobless and Sick, His Son Dies of Starvatior\nNEW YORK.\u2014Because he has been out of work for a long time and\nsick, Nicholas Ceano. a laborer, asked at a police station that his little\nson, who just died, be buried in potter\u2019s field. The worker\u2019s child died\nof malnutrition\u2014that is, starvation.\nAdmits That Crisis Will Continue\nJulius Klein, Assistant Secretary\nof Commerce, took a leaf out of his\nmaster\u2019s notebook, and put his hopes\nfor a business revival off until next\nautumn. This business agent of\nHarper Held in Jail\nTubercular Ward\nSolomon Harper, organizev for the\nAmerican Negro Labor Congress,\narrested and railroaded to prison\nfor three months introducing an\namendment to a resolution on lynch\ning at a meeting called by the\nBrotherhood of Sleeping Car Porters\nhere is confined in the Tuberculosis\nWard in Harts Island Prison. Har\nper would be glad to get letters\nfrom the comrades outside, giving\nhim the news. He is allowed visi\ntors, only one every two weeks.\nThe Randolph clique in the\nPorters\u2019 Union helped to convict\nhim.'\nLabor and Fraternal\n(Organizations\nOffice Worker* Annnnl Dunce.\nJuj\u00bba *4 8, at the Heckacher Roni\nGarden* a1 00th St. and sth Ave. Ad\nmission M\u00bb cents.\n\n1.L.1H Hr. Mok Sunnoodnkl*.\nBa\u00df anil criteriainment Saturday\nJune ?kers Center.\n\nnur.ettl I.L.D. Ilrancb.\nSpring Festival Saturday. June 7\nat -104] Third Ave. (bit. 174th and\n175th jSfiilL Dancing:, games Get\nyour 'ticket*': from your organization,\n\nFrelhrft lliunlelin tlrrlieulrn.\nT.cafh to- nhtv t mandolin. Join\nclasse*. /A rM>l,v rt 106 K 14tli St., oea*\u2019\n('nion Scj.. or at Morning I leiluit of\nfice.\ni gree Mason; Carl George Bachman\nof West Ya., republican, presbyter\nian and long a prosecuting attorney;\nWilliam J. Driver of Arkansas, de\nmocrat and a Mason; Edward\nEverett Eslick of Tennessee, also a\ndemocrat and like Driver, from the\nregion known chiefly for its super\nstition and reactionary \u201cfundamen\ntalism\u201d that forbids the teaching of\nscience in the schools. Fish himself\nis a republican.\nHow reactionary this committee\nis, is admitted by even the bourgeois\npress. The St. Louis \u201cPost-Dispatch\u201d\nof May 26, editorially ridiculing\nWhalen and his forgeries and ques\ntioning the value from the capitalist\nviewpoint of such an \u201cinvestigation,\u2019\nsaid:\n\u201cOn Speaker Longworth\u2019s choice\nof the committee's personnel will\ndepend whether the spirit of tin\ninquiry will be one of hysteria o.\nof reason. The motives of those\nbehind the investigation are in\ndicated by the fact that its spon\nsors are Shell and Fish of New\nYork and Underhill of Massachu\nsetts. We trust Mr. Longworth\nwill choose several more liberal\nspirits than these for the com\nmittee.\u201d\nThat Longworth named Fish as\nthe chairman, shows that the Hoovet\nadministration is choosing \u201chysteria\u201d\nand fascism. The committee has un\nlimited funds and is expected to be\ngin hearings in New York this\n1 Summer.\nto \u201cPrivate Interests\u201d\nwhereby the Muscle Shoals nitrate\nand power resources on the Ten\nnessee river will be leaseA to\n\"private interests\u201d by a leasing\nboard appointed by Wall Street\u2019s\npresident. This plan authorizes a\nfifty-year lease.\nAttorney General by the Sent:\nJudiciary Committee Wednesday f\nthat worthy\u2019s opinion. \u201cFarm\nLabor\u201d Shipstead\u2019s bill permits i\njunctions to be issued where \u201cu\nlawful acts have been threatened\ncommitted.\u201d\nfinance capital found it best to dis\nagree with the ballyhoo optimist\ni who predict a return to \u201cnormalcy\nt I by June or July. There\u2019s no triflir.\nf 1 with a crisis!\nClass for Communist\n1 Fundamental Teacher\ne A class for the preparation o,\n5) i teachers in the fundamentals ol\nCommunism is being formed at the\nn Workers School. Party members,\nwho feel qualified and who wish to\nprepare themselves to teach sunda\ne mentals of Communism should reg\ns I ister at once through the Workers\n_ School for this course. The course\nwill be a thorough one, requiring\nwork and study from those who take\ne j it.\ni- ________\nCommunist Activities\n:t\nBronx V.r.1.. Danre.\nI Saturday, May 31. Bronx Worker\n-1 Center. 680 Prospect Ave. near 140th\nSt. May Day movies.\nParty Member* A**i*ned for Red\nSunday*\nReport to your section hendouar\nterf?. Sunday. June 1 for work in ore\n>e ont circulation campaign of the DaiW\nl\u201e Worker:\nSection 1. 27 E. 4th St.. N. T.; Sec\ntton 2. 1170 Broad wav. N. Y.; Sectioi\n3, 1179 Broad wav. X. Y.: Scot lop 4. 30'\n\\r, Lenox Ave.. N. Y.: Section f\u00bb, 569 Pro*\npect Ave.. Bronx: Section 6. 68 Whin\nnl* St.. Brooklvn: Section 7. 136 l.'th 1\nS Brooklyn: Section 8. 105 Thfttford\n7 Ave.. Brooklyn,\nd\nt A olunteer* for 1.1.. D.\ni. Xeeded. comrades with slight ex\npert* pee In office work to volunteer\ntheir Hervices for working up ntnti\u00ab-\n>i 1 llcjil I-hies. cl*-*., room 430. 7 f, 9 B\u2019wuv.\nW\u00abrk*m \u2018\u2018\u2022\u2022li'uj *t*M*rtv flub.\nMeets pi Pelham yat lion at JO\no clock. Bring your friends.\nSoviet China Is the Doom of the War Lords!\nThe mighty arm of the Her! Army of China will continue to gain\nnr provinces until all China is Soviet! This march of the Red Army\neans the end of all exploiters and tear lords.\nURKHARD LEADS GANG\nTO SUSPEND MILITANT:\nLast night while the executive\nboard of Bakers Local 164, Amalga\nmated Food Workers was in ses\nsion, Burkhard, social fascist lead\ner of the A.F.W., broke in with\nabout 30 henchmen. They threat-\nened the whole executive board with\nphysical beatings and beat up two\nmembers in order to prove that they\nare ready to do it. By this means\nthey forced the executive to suspend\nfor one week Secretary Goepfert, a\nmilitant fighter.\nFood Workers Industrial Union\nThe fact that at the last member\nhip meeting the big majority re\nfused to listen to Burkhard and his\nLovestone henchmen and that the\nmembership almost unanimously\nsupports the representatives of the\nFood Workers Industrial Union has\nmade these fascists afraid of losing\ntheir soft jobs. The membership of\nLocal 164 is working in the shops\nof the A.F. W. where the conditions\nare almost unbelieveable, hours as\nlong as 12, 14 and 15 a day, the\nscale of wages even far below in the\nshops of the A.F.L. which are in\nthemselves very bad.\nLast night Manhattan Lyceum\nwas packed with the membership\nmeeting of the F.W.1.U., in spite of\nthe fact that the weather was bad\nand there was a hurry call for the\nmembership meeting.\n-Nominations for delegates to the j\nA today\u2014\nthe Chinese Soviet Congress^Meets!\nTomorrow\nAll Friends of the Soviet Union Will Hail This Great\nk Event at the Big\n5-Year Plan\nFestival\nULMER PARK\nJ THE PROGRAM INCLUDES: L\nNew Soviet Film Movies of May Day Parade Schenec\ntady Nominating Convention (Film) Athletics by Labor\nJ Sports Union Ukrainian Dancers Concertina Players F\nW. I. R. Brass Band Esfir Less Noted Soviet Singer and\nSpeeches by Louis Hyman H. T. Li. Also Refreshments.\nMOVIES WILL BE TAKEN AND SENT TO U. S. S. R.\nAdmission Fifty Cents\nTickets on Sale at F. S. U. National Office, 175 Fifth Avenue, room 511; Local F. S. U.\n799 Broadway, Room 421; Local IV. I. R., 10 East 17th Street.\nAuspices: FRIENDS OF THE SOVIET UNION\nWORKERS INTERNATIONAL RELIEF\nTo reftch Ulmer Park take 8.-M.T. West End train to 25th Avenue\n\nMAY 31 \u2014DEFEND THE SOVIET UNION DAY!\nDAILY WORKER, NEW YORK. FRIDAY, MAY 30, 1930 7\nMOROS HOLD FORT IN\nFACE OF U. S. MORTAR\nMANILA, P. I. May 28.\u2014The\nAmerican imperialist Philippine\nConstabulary, native mercenaries\nwith the U. S. army officers in com\nmand, today fired 300 mortar shells\nat a fort where a r-ebel group of\nMoros have defied all attempts to\nevict them since May 7.\nThe Moros repulsed every attempt\nto capture the fort, and as night\ncame on, the imperialist troops re\ntreated to Dansalan, a near by\ntown. They were afraid to spend\nthe night in the woods with other\nMoros trying to reinforce the de\nfenders of the fortress.\nR.I.L.U. Congress were held. Out\nof about 50 nominations from the\ndifferent shops and groups, an elim\nination nomination was held result\ning in the following nine: C. Pap\npas, Rappaport, Krane, Tribush.\nSimoli, Eselson, R. Kaplan, Lin\ndenaux, and Joe Roberts. They ar,-1\nto be placed on the national ballo\nwhich will be held in a few days.\nWORKERS\u2019 CENTER\nBARBER SHOP\nMoved to 30 Colon Sqoare\nFREIHEIT BLDG. Main Floni j\niNEEDLE WORKERS\nPLAN CONVENTION\nMany Meets; Enlarge\nShop Delegate Work\nThe, shop delegate council of the\nNeedle Trades Workers Industrial\nUnion met at Stuyvesant Casino\nWednesday night, to act on recom\nmendations to the convention and\nthe election of delegates to the con\nvention from the shop delegate body.\nOne of the recommendations adopted\nwas to transfer many of the re\nj sponsibilities and activities that are\nnow conducted by the business\nagents to the shop delegates, to do\naway with business agents, and in\nstead make paid officers, instead of j\nbeing business agents to attend to\nI the complaints of the union shops\nonly, act as organiers for the union\nand center most of their activities\non the open shops to build shop com\nmittees and unionie these shops.\nOrganize Jobless\nThe plan will come before the con\nvention. Boruchowitz urged the j\ndelegates to develop more initiative\nin the memebership drive and take\nover more responsibility. The dele\ngate stressed the importance of con\ncentrating on open shops. A com\nmittee of five was elected to pro\nceed with the organization of an\nj Unemployed Council. The follow\ni ing delegates were elected to the\ni convention: Hope, Negro organizer\n|of the union; DeFazio, Italian or\nganizer; Harry Nussbaum, Youth\nOrganizer, Weissberg and Kolkin.\nThe New York Council decided to\narrange a welcome concert and ball\nfor the out of town delegates for\nSaturday, June 7th, at New Star\nCasino.\nI Final preparations for the mass\nrank and file convention of the\nNeedle Trades Workers, Industrial\nUnion June 6,7 and 8 are being\nmade. On Tuesday, June 3, at 8\no\u2019clock, the New York General Ex\necutive Board will meet to act on\nthe program for future work to be\nsubmitted to the convention. Fri\nday afternoon, June 6, the full\nG.E.8., including the out of town\nmembers will meet at the office of\nthe union, 131 West 28th Street.\nAt 8 o\u2019clock in the evening on Fri\nday, June 6th, the official opening\nof the convention will take place at\nNew Star Casino, 107 St. and Park\nAve. Reports are coming in from\nthe out of town centers of the elec\nj Con of a large number of delegates\nfrom organized as well as unor\nganized shops.\nFOR RENT\u2014\nI.AKKE ROOM AXD KITCHEN Co\non.rntivr. 2800 llronx Park Gait,\nF 52, Olinvillr SOOT.\nI.IHGK ROOM. LIGHT. AIRY. In\nquire Slaklml. 45 G. 7th At., 3rd floor.\ni LARGE AIRY ROOM. TWO WIN\nDOWS. ONE BLOCK FROM BEACH.\nPHONE SHEEPSHEAD 9204.\nMason Story \u201cAt the Villa\nRose\u201d at Cameo Theatre\n\u201cAt the Villa Rose,\u201d a talking!\nscreen adaptation of A. E. V. Ma- 1\nson\u2019s mystery novel by the same\nname, is having its American pro- j\nmiere at the Cameo Theatre this. j\nweek.\nThe talking picture, as in Mason\u2019s j\ntreatment, deals with the maneu- i;\nversos Hanaud, the French detec-1 i\ntive, and follows him through many j\nthrilling episodes, to the solution oi\nthe murder \u201cAt the Villa Rose.\u201d\n\u201cAt the Villa Rose\u201d was adapted\nfor the screen by Julius Hagen and\nHenry Edwards, and was directed\nby Leslie Hiscott. The featured play\ners in the cast are: Austin Trevor, j\nRichard Cooper, and Norah Baring, t\nc\nSHOE WORKERS\nPICK DELEGATES\nGENERAL MEMBERSHIP MEET-\nING LINES OUT ORGANIZATION\nCAMPAIGN I I\nAt a geperal membership meeting! t\n16 West 21st St., Wednesday, F. G. ji\nBiedenkapp, General Manager of the j\nIndependent Shoe Workers Union,\ngave a lengthy report on the crisis\nwhich the union had gone through j\nduring the lock-out period against\nthe shoe workers which was instig-\nated by the infamous Chas G. Woods\nof the U. S. Labor Department. j\nBiedenkapp made a number of\nproposals in the name of the Ex-\necutive Committee and called upon j t\nall members to become active in i j\nreorganizing the forces of the Union, j\nJ. Magliacano who, due to the.\nillness of Biedenkapp, is now acting 1\nas general organizer, also gave a\nreport. He urged all the workers j 1\nto unite all the forces and renew f\ntheir activity, and held build a pow-\nerful National Shoe Leather j\nWorkers Union in the United States.j\nA recommendation of the Execut-1\nive Committee to elect fifteen mem- j\nbers of open shops to the Joint Coun\ncil was accepted, and they were elec\nted. Six shoe workers were nomin\nated out which two will go to the\nR.I.L.U. Congress. c\nAll the Shoe Workers are also 1\nurged to participate in the hike of 1\nCity Workers Clubs, Friday. All t\nwill meet at 9 P. M. at the end of t\nthe Jerome Ave. line bound for c\nTibbets.\n\u2666AMUIEMENTf\nA Theatre Gnlld Prodnctiun '\u201c\u201d1 I1 \u2018T l'J\u2018lf TJM Iflllllff.Ol\nHOTEL UNIVERSE xtwmm\u00df\nBy PHILIP BARKY I SENSATIONAL MYSTERY\nMARTIN thriller\nE and \u201cAT THE VILLA ROSE\u2019\u2019\nTHREE LITTLE GIRLS\" sip\u2122\nMYSTERY\u2019\nOnUDEKI EvJS BtSO. Mats* Wed. and with\nSat. !>\u00bb3O. Rottr- Cmnpxon and Lowell Sherman 1\nmusic\njut.. Thanday and Saturday at g:3o Forward to Mass Conference\nXOPAZE Against Unemployment, Chicago\nCamedy Hit from the French July 4th.\nwith THANK MORGAN, Phoebe Foater,\nClarence Derwent ________\nNOW PLAYING! i\nA FIRST film of the five-year PLAN a\nAmerican premiere! a Great Film Record of\nMOM M IhIAF \u25a0H% a Great Soviet Achieve-\nB LIIr IT%IK ment! The Building of\nI BBVrIpEIIF the Turkestan Siberian\n\u201cPride of Soviet clnwnntOKrnphy\u201d Railroad T\nIZ VESTIA AVCUIL Wttu\nBTH STREET etLAYHOUSE *\"oVh\\vl: j\nFILM GUILD It. FLIESLEIt.\nCINEMA Mona\u00dflnK Director SPRIhr 50 8 5\nEAST SIDE THEATRES\n2' ndTav enup\nPLAYHOUSE\n133 SECOND AVENUE, CORNER EIGHTH STREET\nTo honor the arrival of EISENSTEIN. the famous film\ndirector of \u2022\u25a0POTEMKIN\u201d and \u201cTEN DAYS THAT SHOOK\n